<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 20 at 6:01PM EDT until July 20 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 615 PM EDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN ST. CLAIR COUNTY...
At 601 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Port Huron,
moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Port Huron, Fort Gratiot and Wadhams.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
